<subSubSection id="C3296509FFACFF91FF4DFE43FCEC7724" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B8C3682FFACFF91FF4DFE43FC3A712A" blockId="5.[144,1127,356,1063]" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FF4DFE43FE9F72A3" authorityName=", Schenck" authorityYear="1853" box="[144,369,390,416]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvicornis">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FF4DFE43FE9F72A3" box="[144,369,390,416]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">Andrena fulvicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
est comprise dans le sous-genre 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FD3FFE43FC1B72A3" authority="Perez, 1890" authorityName="Perez" authorityYear="1890" box="[738,1013,390,416]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Notandrena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FD3FFE43FC8772A3" box="[738,873,390,416]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">Notandrena</emphasis>
Pérez, 1890
</taxonomicName>
. Elle a été décrite pour la première fois par Schenck en 1853, avant que son nom soit synonymisé avec 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FF14FE0EFE8172E7" authorityName=", Schenck" authorityYear="1853" box="[201,367,458,485]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidiuscula">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FF14FE0EFE8172E7" box="[201,367,458,485]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">A. nitidiuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
par 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B73FFACFF91FE7DFE0FFDB872E6" author="Warncke K." box="[416,598,458,485]" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" pagination="171 - 318" refId="ref4948" refString="Warncke K. 1967. Beitrag zur Klarung palaarktischer Andrena - Arten (Hym. Apidae). Eos 43: 171 - 318." type="journal article" year="1967">Warncke (1967)</bibRefCitation>
. Finalement, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B73FFACFF91FD31FE0FFB8C72E6" author="Schmid-Egger C. &amp; Doczkal D." box="[748,1122,458,485]" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref4710" refString="Schmid-Egger C. &amp; Doczkal D. 1995. Der taxonomische Status von Andrena fulvicornis Schenck, 1853 (Hymenoptera, Apidae). Entomofauna 16: 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1995">Schmid-Egger &amp; Doczkal (1995)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B73FFACFF91FF4DFE29FDF27105" author="Schmid-Egger C. &amp; Scheuchl E." box="[144,540,492,518]" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" refId="ref4806" refString="Schmid-Egger C. &amp; Scheuchl E. 1997. Illustrierte Bestimmungstabellen der Wildbienen Deutschlands und Osterreichs unter Berucksichtigung der Arten der Schweiz. Band III: Schlussel der Arten der Familie Andrenidae. Selbstverlag. Velden, 180 pp." type="book" year="1997">Schmid-Egger &amp; Scheuchl (1997)</bibRefCitation>
et 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B73FFACFF91FD99FE29FCD47105" author="Schwenninger H." box="[580,826,492,518]" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" pagination="1945 - 1962" refId="ref4900" refString="Schwenninger H. 2013. Festlegung von Typen fur Andrena nitidiuscula Schenck 1853 und Andrena fulvicornis Schenck 1861 sowie Erstnachweis von Andrena curvana Warncke, 1965 fur Deutschland (Hymenoptera, Andrenidae, Andrena, Subgenus Notandrena). Linzer biologische Beitrage 45: 1945 - 1962." type="journal article" year="2013">Schwenninger (2013)</bibRefCitation>
ont confirmé le statut de 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FF4DFDCAFEC2712B" authorityName=", Schenck" authorityYear="1853" box="[144,300,526,553]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvicornis">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FF4DFDCAFEC2712B" box="[144,300,526,553]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">A. fulvicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comme espèce à part entière, différente de 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FCF9FDCAFC23712B" authorityName=", Schenck" authorityYear="1853" box="[804,973,526,553]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidiuscula">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FCF9FDCAFC23712B" box="[804,973,526,553]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">A. nitidiuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8C3682FFACFF91FF11FDF5FCEC7724" blockId="5.[144,1127,356,1063]" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">
Globalement, ces deux espèces sont très proches l’une de l’autre. D’un point de vue biologique, elles habitent toutes les deux des endroits chauds et secs (prairies, vignes, carrières) et sont oligolectiques sur 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FDA5FDB1FB8C718C" authority="(Schmid-Egger &amp; Doczkal 1995)" baseAuthorityName="Schmid-Egger &amp; Doczkal" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[632,1122,628,655]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">
Apiaceae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B73FFACFF91FD2DFDB1FBB5718C" author="Schmid-Egger C. &amp; Doczkal D." box="[752,1115,628,655]" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref4710" refString="Schmid-Egger C. &amp; Doczkal D. 1995. Der taxonomische Status von Andrena fulvicornis Schenck, 1853 (Hymenoptera, Apidae). Entomofauna 16: 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1995">Schmid-Egger &amp; Doczkal 1995</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Leur grande différence réside dans leur phénologie, 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FD26FD52FC4871B3" authorityName=", Schenck" authorityYear="1853" box="[763,934,662,689]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidiuscula">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FD26FD52FC4871B3" box="[763,934,662,689]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">A. nitidiuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
étant univoltine (une génération de fin juin à fin août) et 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FDBCFD7CFD1071D1" authorityName=", Schenck" authorityYear="1853" box="[609,766,696,723]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvicornis">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FDBCFD7CFD1071D1" box="[609,766,696,723]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">A. fulvicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bivoltine (1 
<superScript id="7C469BCAFFACFF91FC5AFD7DFC7271C5" attach="left" box="[903,924,696,710]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">ère</superScript>
génération de fin avril à mi-juin et 2 
<superScript id="7C469BCAFFACFF91FEB0FD1FFE9A71EB" attach="left" box="[365,372,730,744]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">e</superScript>
génération de début juillet à fin août (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B73FFACFF91FCEAFD1FFF247014" author="Schmid-Egger C. &amp; Doczkal D." pageId="5" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref4710" refString="Schmid-Egger C. &amp; Doczkal D. 1995. Der taxonomische Status von Andrena fulvicornis Schenck, 1853 (Hymenoptera, Apidae). Entomofauna 16: 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1995">Schmid-Egger &amp; Doczkal 1995</bibRefCitation>
). Concernant la morphologie, plusieurs différences existent (ponctuation du 1 
<superScript id="7C469BCAFFACFF91FB84FD39FB887009" attach="none" box="[1113,1126,764,778]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">er</superScript>
tergite et du scutellum, couleur des articles antennaires, etc.), 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B73FFACFF91FCE6FCDBFF367059" author="Schmid-Egger C. &amp; Scheuchl E." pageId="5" pageNumber="74" refId="ref4806" refString="Schmid-Egger C. &amp; Scheuchl E. 1997. Illustrierte Bestimmungstabellen der Wildbienen Deutschlands und Osterreichs unter Berucksichtigung der Arten der Schweiz. Band III: Schlussel der Arten der Familie Andrenidae. Selbstverlag. Velden, 180 pp." type="book" year="1997">Schmid-Egger &amp; Scheuchl (1997)</bibRefCitation>
ayant très bien résumé ces informations dans leur clé des 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FC5BFC85FBE07059" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[902,1038,832,858]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Andrenidae</taxonomicName>
d’Alle- magne, d’Autriche et de 
<collectingCountry id="F3247612FFACFF91FE6EFCA7FDEE707F" box="[435,512,866,892]" name="Switzerland" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">Suisse</collectingCountry>
. La femelle capturée en 
<collectingCountry id="F3247612FFACFF91FCF8FCA7FC81707F" box="[805,879,866,892]" name="Switzerland" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">Suisse</collectingCountry>
correspond parfaitement aux descriptions d’ 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FE76FC40FDA6709D" authorityName=", Schenck" authorityYear="1853" box="[427,584,900,927]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvicornis">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FE76FC40FDA6709D" box="[427,584,900,927]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">A. fulvicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, en particulier les antennes orange et la ponctuation comparativement dense du scutellum. Les séquences obtenues sont à 99.85% identiques à 2 séquences obtenus d’individus de 
<collectingCountry id="F3247612FFACFF91FD16FC0DFCCA70E1" box="[715,804,968,994]" name="Turkey" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">Turquie</collectingCountry>
et à 99.69 % identiques à 4 séquences obtenues d’individus d’Allemagne. La distance génétique avec 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FF4DFBC8FED77725" authorityName=", Schenck" authorityYear="1853" box="[144,313,1036,1063]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidiuscula">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FF4DFBC8FED77725" box="[144,313,1036,1063]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">A. nitidiuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
est de 5.21% (1 individu d’Allemagne).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3296509FFACFF92FF4DFBB7FE8273D6" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8C3682FFACFF91FF4DFBB7FE16778E" blockId="5.[144,1128,1138,1675]" box="[144,504,1138,1165]" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FF4DFBB7FE16778E" bold="true" box="[144,504,1138,1165]" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">
Richesse des prairies du 
<collectingRegion id="49F7F860FFACFF91FE62FBB6FE16778E" box="[447,504,1139,1165]" country="Switzerland" name="Jura" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">Jura</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8C3682FFACFF92FF4DFB50FE8273D6" blockId="5.[144,1128,1138,1675]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1136,152,1438]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">
Le site de Glovelier a montré une richesse spécifique très intéressante. En effet, en plus de deux nouvelles espèces pour la 
<collectingCountry id="F3247612FFACFF91FDCBFB72FD8C77D2" box="[534,610,1207,1233]" name="Switzerland" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">Suisse</collectingCountry>
, plusieurs espèces rares ont été trouvées dans ces pâturages. Il s’agit notamment de 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FDE6FB1CFC2877F0" authority="Morawitz, 1866" authorityName="Morawitz" authorityYear="1866" box="[571,966,1241,1267]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schencki">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FDE6FB1CFCE677F0" box="[571,776,1241,1267]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">Andrena schencki</emphasis>
Morawitz, 1866
</taxonomicName>
, dont la population trouvée est probablement une des dernières de 
<collectingCountry id="F3247612FFACFF91FD2EFB3EFCD17616" box="[755,831,1275,1301]" name="Switzerland" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">Suisse</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FC96FB3EFF3D7634" authority="(Kirby, 1802)" baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labialis">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FC96FB3EFBE57616" box="[843,1035,1275,1301]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">Andrena labialis</emphasis>
(Kirby, 1802)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FF39FAD8FD777634" authority="(Fabricius, 1793)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[228,665,1309,1335]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Bombus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="veteranus">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FF39FAD8FE2F7635" box="[228,449,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">Bombus veteranus</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 1793)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FD76FAD8FB8C7634" authority="(Fabricius, 1775)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[683,1122,1308,1335]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Bombus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruderatus">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FD76FAD8FC677634" box="[683,905,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">Bombus ruderatus</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 1775)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FF4DFAFAFDBA7659" authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[144,596,1343,1370]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Bombus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subterraneus">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FF4DFAFAFE62765A" box="[144,396,1343,1369]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">Bombus subterraneus</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
ou encore 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FD0EFAFAFF257678" authority="Spinola, 1808" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1808" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Rophites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinquespinosus">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FD0EFAFAFBEE765A" box="[723,1024,1343,1369]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">Rophites quinquespinosus</emphasis>
Spinola, 1808
</taxonomicName>
. Un individu de 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FE57FAA4FD157678" authority="Fabricius, 1804" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1804" box="[394,763,1377,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Nomada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigma">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FE57FAA4FDAE7678" box="[394,576,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">Nomada stigma</emphasis>
Fabricius, 1804
</taxonomicName>
, une espèce qui n’avait plus été observée depuis plus de 20 ans, a aussi été capturé. Cette abeille coucou utilise 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FF4DFA60FEBD76BC" baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[144,339,1445,1471]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labialis">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FF4DFA60FEBD76BC" box="[144,339,1445,1471]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">Andrena labialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FEABFA60FDA676BC" authorityName="Morawitz" authorityYear="1866" box="[374,584,1445,1471]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schencki">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FEABFA60FDA676BC" box="[374,584,1445,1471]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">Andrena schencki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comme hôte. En-dehors des conditions climatiques propices aux abeilles sauvages, cette richesse exceptionnelle s’explique probablement par la grande diversité du paysage et la présence de plusieurs grands pâ- turages extensifs dans un rayon assez proche (moins de 
<quantity id="4CCB9B67FFACFF91FCC1F9CEFCB57525" box="[796,859,1547,1574]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" unit="km" value="2.0">2 km</quantity>
). Ces grandes surfaces de pâtures constituent une offre en fleurs importante qui favorise le maintien de population de taille importante, comme c’est le cas pour 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FCEBF98AFC5E756A" baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[822,944,1615,1641]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labialis">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FCEBF98AFC5E756A" box="[822,944,1615,1641]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">A. labialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFACFF91FC0AF98AFBB1756A" authorityName="Morawitz" authorityYear="1866" box="[983,1119,1615,1641]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schencki">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFACFF91FC0AF98AFBB1756A" box="[983,1119,1615,1641]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="74">A. schencki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, deux espèces qui semblent bénéficier directement de la présence de grands champs de trèfles (trèfles blancs pour 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FE21FF5DFD6B73B1" authorityName="Morawitz" authorityYear="1866" box="[508,645,152,178]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schencki">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FE21FF5DFD6B73B1" box="[508,645,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">A. schencki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et trèfles rouges pour 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FC4BFF5DFBFF73B1" baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[918,1041,152,178]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labialis">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FC4BFF5DFBFF73B1" box="[918,1041,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">A. labialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
d’après nos observations).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3296509FFAFFF92FF09FF19FC04769D" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B8C3682FFAFFF92FF09FF19FC04769D" blockId="6.[151,1136,152,1438]" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FF09FF19FDB673F5" authority=", Illiger, 1806" authorityName=", Illiger" authorityYear="1806" box="[212,600,220,246]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stragulata">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FF09FF19FE5073F5" box="[212,446,220,246]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">Andrena stragulata,</emphasis>
Illiger, 1806
</taxonomicName>
, a été observée en assez grand nombre sur le site de Glovelier, et de manière isolée sur le site d’Undervelier. Il est probable à nos yeux que cette espèce représente la génération de printemps de 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FCA9FEE5FB807239" authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" box="[884,1134,288,315]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rosae">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FCA9FEE5FC3A7239" box="[884,980,288,314]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">A. rosae</emphasis>
Panzer, 1801
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B73FFAFFF92FF42FE87FE6C725F" author="Reemer M. &amp; Groenenberg D. S. J. &amp; van Achterberg C. &amp; Peeters T. M. J." box="[159,386,322,349]" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" pagination="21 - 32" refId="ref4657" refString="Reemer M., Groenenberg D. S. J., van Achterberg C. &amp; Peeters T. M. J. 2008. Taxonomic assessment of Andrena rosae and A. stragulata by DNAsequencing (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Andrenidae). Entomologia Generalis 31: 21 - 32." type="journal article" year="2008">Reemer et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B73FFAFFF92FE52FE87FD9D725E" author="Schmidt S. &amp; Schmid-Egger C. &amp; Moriniere J. &amp; Haszprunar G. &amp; Hebert P. D." box="[399,627,322,349]" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" pagination="985 - 1000" refId="ref4846" refString="Schmidt S., Schmid-Egger C., Moriniere J., Haszprunar G. &amp; Hebert P. D. 2015. DNA barcoding largely supports 250 years of classical taxonomy: identifications for Central European bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea partim). Molecular ecology resources 15: 985 - 1000." type="journal article" year="2015">Schmidt et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
, voir aussi 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B73FFAFFF92FD24FE87FC4F725F" author="Westrich P." box="[761,929,322,348]" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref4973" refString="Westrich P. 2014. Beitrag zur Diskussion uber den taxonomischen Status von Andrena rosae Panzer 1801 (Hymenoptera, Apidae). Eucera 8: 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="2014">Westrich 2014</bibRefCitation>
), malgré la différence morphologique marquée entre les mâles de ces deux formes (
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FC43FEA0FBDB727D" authorityName=", Illiger" authorityYear="1806" box="[926,1077,356,383]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stragulata">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FC43FEA0FBDB727D" box="[926,1077,356,383]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">A. stragulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possède une forte dent sous la joue, alors que cette dent est généralement absente chez 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FF4AFE6CFF1972C1" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" box="[151,247,425,451]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rosae">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FF4AFE6CFF1972C1" box="[151,247,425,451]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">A. rosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). En été, 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FEB1FE6CFE2072C1" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" box="[364,462,425,451]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rosae">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FEB1FE6CFE2072C1" box="[364,462,425,451]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">A. rosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
était entièrement absente du site de Glovelier mais assez abondante sur le site de Undervelier, situé à 
<quantity id="4CCB9B67FFAFFF92FD6BFE0FFD1F72E7" box="[694,753,458,485]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" unit="km" value="5.0">5 km</quantity>
du site de Glovelier. Alors que 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FF4AFE28FEC07105" authorityName=", Illiger" authorityYear="1806" box="[151,302,492,519]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stragulata">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FF4AFE28FEC07105" box="[151,302,492,519]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">A. stragulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(ou la génération printanière de 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FD7AFE28FCEB7105" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" box="[679,773,493,519]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rosae">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FD7AFE28FCEB7105" box="[679,773,493,519]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">A. rosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) est polylectique, la génération d’été de 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FF21FDCAFEB1712B" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" box="[252,351,527,553]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rosae">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FF21FDCAFEB1712B" box="[252,351,527,553]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">A. rosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
semble oligolectique sur les 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FD67FDCBFC02712B" authority="(Westrich 2014)" baseAuthorityName="Westrich" baseAuthorityYear="2014" box="[698,1004,526,552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">
Apiaceae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B73FFAFFF92FCEBFDCBFC0A712B" author="Westrich P." box="[822,996,526,552]" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref4973" refString="Westrich P. 2014. Beitrag zur Diskussion uber den taxonomischen Status von Andrena rosae Panzer 1801 (Hymenoptera, Apidae). Eucera 8: 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="2014">Westrich 2014</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Le site de Glovelier était particulièrement sec en juillet et par conséquent entièrement dépourvu d’Apiaceae, ce qui peut expliquer l’absence de la génération d’été de 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FC72FD96FBE1716F" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" box="[943,1039,595,621]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rosae">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FC72FD96FBE1716F" box="[943,1039,595,621]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">A. rosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
dans ce site. L’absence d’une des générations sur les sites de nidification de l’autre génération n’est probablement pas une preuve de leur appartenance à deux espèces biologiques distinctes. Cette assez grande espèce est probablement très mobile et en l’absence de plantes-hôtes, les individus de deuxième génération trouvent probablement des sites favorables dans des habitats plus frais. Ces deux espèces sont rares à très rares en 
<collectingCountry id="F3247612FFAFFF92FF4AFCDBFF0F703B" box="[151,225,798,824]" name="Switzerland" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">Suisse</collectingCountry>
et le fait qu’elles soient les deux assez communes dans les sites proches de Glovelier et d’Undervelier nous semble un début de preuve de leur appartenance à une espèce. De manière similaire, un mâle de 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FDB9FCA6FC3E707E" authority="(Kirby, 1802)" baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[612,976,867,893]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinigera">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FDB9FCA6FCDC707F" box="[612,818,867,893]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">Andrena spinigera</emphasis>
(Kirby, 1802)
</taxonomicName>
, espèce quasi- ment inconnue du Nord de la 
<collectingCountry id="F3247612FFAFFF92FE33FC40FDD6709C" box="[494,568,901,927]" name="Switzerland" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">Suisse</collectingCountry>
, a été découvert dans le site de Glovelier. Il s’agit probablement de la génération printanière de l’espèce connue sous le nom de 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FBD0FC62FE4670E0" authority="Kirby, 1802" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trimmerana">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FBD0FC62FEF270E1" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">Andrena trimmerana</emphasis>
Kirby, 1802
</taxonomicName>
, pour laquelle quelques données isolées existent dans le Nord de la 
<collectingCountry id="F3247612FFAFFF92FF6FFC2EFF127706" box="[178,252,1003,1029]" name="Switzerland" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">Suisse</collectingCountry>
. Ce mâle présente des tergites à cuticule entièrement brune, contrairement aux spécimens du Sud des Alpes qui ont les tergites rouges. Son appartenance à 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FC3AFBC8FB837724" baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[999,1133,1037,1063]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinigera">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FC3AFBC8FB837724" box="[999,1133,1037,1063]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">A. spinigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(ou à la génération printanière de 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FDC2FBEAFD2A774A" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1802" box="[543,708,1071,1097]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trimmerana">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FDC2FBEAFD2A774A" box="[543,708,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">A. trimmerana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) est claire si les critères de la clé de 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B73FFAFFF92FF4AFB94FDFB7768" author="Schmid-Egger C. &amp; Scheuchl E." box="[151,533,1105,1131]" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" refId="ref4806" refString="Schmid-Egger C. &amp; Scheuchl E. 1997. Illustrierte Bestimmungstabellen der Wildbienen Deutschlands und Osterreichs unter Berucksichtigung der Arten der Schweiz. Band III: Schlussel der Arten der Familie Andrenidae. Selbstverlag. Velden, 180 pp." type="book" year="1997">Schmid-Egger &amp; Scheuchl (1997)</bibRefCitation>
sont utilisés: sternum 8 avec émargination profonde; joue pourvue d’une longue épine; mandibule se terminant en pointe, sans dent préapicale. Une femelle de la génération d’été de 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FDE0FB50FD0C77AC" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1802" box="[573,738,1173,1199]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trimmerana">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FDE0FB50FD0C77AC" box="[573,738,1173,1199]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">A. trimmerana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a été capturée sur le site de Undervelier le 
<date id="FF8D1042FFAFFF92FF28FB72FE6877D1" box="[245,390,1207,1234]" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" value="2015-07-07">7 juillet 2015</date>
; cette identification a été vérifée au moyen de barcode ADN. Géné- tiquement, les deux spécimens (
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FDD4FB1FFCE877F0" authority="de Glovelier" authorityName="de Glovelier" box="[521,774,1241,1267]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinigera">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FDD4FB1FFD9F77F0" box="[521,625,1242,1267]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">spinigera</emphasis>
de Glovelier
</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FCF3FB1FFB8977F7" authority="de Undervelier" authorityName="de Undervelier" box="[814,1127,1241,1268]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trimmerana">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FCF3FB1FFC5D77F0" box="[814,947,1242,1267]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">trimmerana</emphasis>
de Undervelier
</taxonomicName>
) sont très proches l’un de l’autre (distance génétique de 0.015%) mais clairement distincts d’un spécimen de 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FEB9FAD8FD757634" authority="de Glovelier" authorityName="de Glovelier" box="[356,667,1309,1335]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carantonica">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FEB9FAD8FDE57634" box="[356,523,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">A. carantonica</emphasis>
de Glovelier
</taxonomicName>
(distance génétique 1.5 %). A nouveau, la présence au niveau régional de 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FE2EFAFAFD97765A" box="[499,633,1343,1369]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinigera">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FE2EFAFAFD97765A" box="[499,633,1343,1369]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">A. spinigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAFFF92FD46FAFAFCD0765A" box="[667,830,1343,1369]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trimmerana">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAFFF92FD46FAFAFCD0765A" box="[667,830,1343,1369]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">A. trimmerana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
dans deux sites proches du 
<collectingRegion id="49F7F860FFAFFF92FF4AFAA7FF27767F" box="[151,201,1378,1404]" country="Switzerland" name="Jura" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">Jura</collectingRegion>
, alors qu’elles sont très rares ailleurs en 
<collectingCountry id="F3247612FFAFFF92FD59FAA4FD207678" box="[644,718,1377,1403]" name="Switzerland" pageId="6" pageNumber="75">Suisse</collectingCountry>
, suggère que ces deux formes sont en fait les deux générations d’une seule espèce biologique (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B73FFAFFF92FCD9FA46FC33769D" author="Schmidt S. &amp; Schmid-Egger C. &amp; Moriniere J. &amp; Haszprunar G. &amp; Hebert P. D." box="[772,989,1411,1438]" pageId="6" pageNumber="75" pagination="985 - 1000" refId="ref4846" refString="Schmidt S., Schmid-Egger C., Moriniere J., Haszprunar G. &amp; Hebert P. D. 2015. DNA barcoding largely supports 250 years of classical taxonomy: identifications for Central European bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea partim). Molecular ecology resources 15: 985 - 1000." type="journal article" year="2015">Schmidt et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
